Class Table

  • java.lang.Object
    • Table
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Table
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class implements relational database tables (including attribute names, domains and a list of tuples. Five basic relational algebra operators are provided: project, select, union, minus join. The insert data manipulation operator is also provided. Missing are update and delete data manipulation operators.
    See Also:

      • compareOperation

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Comparable[]> compareOperation(Table table2,
                                                               java.lang.String operation)
        Compare the tables to each other, if the operation is minus, complete the relational algebra minus operation. If the operation is union, complete the relational algebra union operation. #usage movie.compareOperation (show)
        Parameters:
        table2 - The rhs table in the minus operation
        operation - The string containing either the word 'union' or 'minus' specifiying which operation needs to be completed
        Returns:
        a List representing either the difference or the union appropriately

      • join

        public Table join(java.lang.String attributes1,
                  java.lang.String attributes2,
                  Table table2)
        Join this table and table2 by performing an equijoin. Tuples from both tables are compared requiring attributes1 to equal attributes2. Disambiguate attribute names by append "2" to the end of any duplicate attribute name. #usage movie.join ("studioNo", "name", studio) #usage movieStar.join ("name == s.name", starsIn)
        Parameters:
        attributes1 - the attributes of this table to be compared (Foreign Key)
        attributes2 - the attributes of table2 to be compared (Primary Key)
        table2 - the rhs table in the join operation
        Returns:
        a table with tuples satisfying the equality predicate
